parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty ABS sensors can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system activates unnecessarily
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes make a buzzing noise
the vehicle slides or loses control when braking.

the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes make a noise
the vehicle slides or loses control when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccessible brake fluid container can make it difficult or impossible to check or refill the brake fluid, leading to brake system failure and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty checking or refilling brake fluid
brake system failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition passlock/passkey security system can cause the vehicle to not restart, leaving the driver stranded and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle will not restart
dash lights may appear
the brake and ABS indicator lights may illuminate
and the vehicle may only restart after waiting 15-30 minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window can cause a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents, and create a hazardous situation for the vehicle's occupants.
symptoms: The power window may go down partially
not go out
or only go up a small amount
and the problem may be intermittent or permanent.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Stop Lamp and Rear Hazard Lamp Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stop lamp and rear hazard lamp can cause a failure to warn following drivers that the vehicle is braking or stopped, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The stop lamps and rear hazard lamps become inoperative
but the center high-mounted stop lamp and turn signal functions are not affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fire can cause the vehicle to catch fire, potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: White smoke may come from the dash immediately after starting the vehicle
and the vehicle may be destroyed by an electrical fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause a loss of power steering assist, leading to hard steering efforts, and in some cases, brake failure, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Hard steering efforts
power steering failure without warning
brake failure
vibration when applying brakes
rattling windows when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Longer stopping distances
vibration when applying brakes
rattling windows when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaks in the steering fluid pump can cause a loss of power steering assist, leading to hard steering efforts, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Steering fluid leaks
rust coming through paint.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the electrical and ignition system can cause problems with the vehicle's overall operation, potentially leading to accidents or breakdowns.
symptoms: Replaced carburetor
ignition coil
and rotor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the door locking and hatchback mechanisms can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety risks.
symptoms: Doors do not lock manually
cannot open back hatch.
